How can I modify the following C++ code to print out all odd numbers between 1-20 excluding the ones divisible by 3?
for(int i=1; i<=20; i++){
  if(i%2!=0){
    cout<<i<<" ";
  }
}

To modify the C++ code so that it prints all odd numbers between 1 and 20, excluding those divisible by 3, you can add an additional condition to the `if` statement to check for divisibility by 3. Here's how you can do it:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    for(int i = 1; i <= 20; i++) {
        if(i % 2 != 0 && i % 3 != 0) {
            cout << i << " ";
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```

In this modified code, the condition `i % 2 != 0` checks if the number is odd, and `i % 3 != 0` ensures the number is not divisible by 3. If both conditions are true, the number is printed.
